hopobject.body: I want to make a withdrawal duramale vs climinax When Amazon.com founder Jeff Bezos bought the Washington Post for $250 million earlier this month, he bought a lot of problems, but none of them had to do with pension funds. That's in large part because the Post was lucky enough to have Buffett as a board member, investor and adviser for many years, and smart enough to take his advice. The result: a pension fund with $1.4 billion in obligations and $2.4 billion in assets.
